#   POST tickets: commit / fast-forward / push

`be post` advances the current branch ‚Äî worktree‚Üírepo commit and/or fast-forward push, recursing into mounted submodules. Tickets below tighten its commit-message handling, push transports, and no-op reporting. Each entry is one active ticket with its live state; an entry drops off once the whole ticket lands (landed commits stay on the board's POST line). The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [POST-016] ‚Äî **CRITICAL.** `be post` sweeps stray/unstaged worktree files into the commit: a `be put <one-file>` + `be post` committed the staged file PLUS unrelated dirty files (`sniff/*`, `test/patch/*`) left over from a prior failed `be patch`, contaminating `?main` (the test dirs land as `mis`). Commit scope must be EXACTLY the staged set (selective) or the genuinely-dirty set ‚Äî never tree entries with no on-disk file, never partial-patch leftovers.
 -  [POST-006] ‚Äî `POSTCFLCT` false-fires on conflict-marker strings in tracked source comments/literals (e.g. `sniff/PATCH.c:339`), forcing a blunt `--force`. Recognize only the real WEAVE output shape, not any inline `<<<<‚Ä¶||||‚Ä¶>>>>` occurrence.

